      • checkForWinner

        public static boolean checkForWinner​(int[][] sudokuContents)

        This is the master method, acting as a coordinator for the lower-level methods.

        A sudoku is solved, when the following conditions are met:
        • Every row contains every number from 1 to 9 exactly once
        • Every column contains every number from 1 to 9 exactly once
        • Every 3x3 cell contains every number from 1 to 9 exactly once
        Parameters:
        sudokuContents - The contents of a sudoku in a two-dimensional array.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the sudoku is solved, othewise returns false.

      • legal

        public static boolean legal​(int[][] sudokuContents,
                            int x,
                            int y)

        NOT IMPLEMENTED YET! Designed for slightly more efficient legality checks on the sudoku.

        The basic principle is: Assuming our sudoku had no illegal entries before the last entry and assuming that only one number was changed, then we only have to check if the single row, the single column and the single cell that number exists in is legal.
        Parameters:
        sudokuContents - Contents of the sudoku to be checked.
        x - -axis coordinate of the last number to be changed.
        y - -axis coordinat of the last number to be changed.
        Returns:
        Returns true, if the contents of the row, column and cell of given coordinate are legal.

      • checkNumberSetForCompletion

        public static boolean checkNumberSetForCompletion​(int[] numberSet)

        Parameters:
        numberSet - A set of 9 integers.
        Returns:

      • findNextUnknown

        public static int[] findNextUnknown​(int[][] sudokuContents,
                                    int x,
                                    int y)
        Finds the next empty cell in the sudoku. 'Next' is determined by first row, then column. Note: If you want to find the first unknown in the entire sudoku, set the parameter y to a negative number.
        Parameters:
        sudokuContents - Contents of a sudoku.
        x - We are looking for the next unknown cell after x
        y - We are looking for the next unknown cell after y
        Returns:
        Returns an array of two integers, the x and y values of the next unknown cell.
